.START 

Krug International Inc. of Dayton, Ohio, said its Krug International Ltd. unit received a contract from the Tripod-Laing Joint Venture of the U.K. to provide physiological training equipment for an aeromedical center. 

Specific terms weren't disclosed, but Krug said under the multimillion-dollar contract that it will provide pilot training equipment.
Krug said its Technology Systems division, based in Dayton, is responsible for technical support. 

Tripod-Laing is a joint venture between Tripod Engineering Ltd., an engineering company, and a unit of John Laing Construction Ltd., both of London, a spokeswoman at Krug said. 

In addition to its involvement in aerospace testing and research, Krug also makes housewares and garden products. 

